#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="an4.188"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an4.188:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 4 "
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 4 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an4.188:0.2"
msgid "19. Brāhmaṇavagga "
msgstr "19. Brahmins "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "an4.188:0.3"
msgid "188. Upakasutta "
msgstr "188. With Upaka "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "an4.188:1.1"
msgid "Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā rājagahe viharati gijjhakūṭe pabbate. "
msgstr "Once the Buddha was staying near Rājagaha, on the Vulture’s Peak Mountain. "

msgctxt "an4.188:1.2"
msgid "Atha kho upako maṇḍikāputto yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho upako maṇḍikāputto bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then Upaka the son of Maṇḍikā went up to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, and said to him: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli2.182, sc2
msgctxt "an4.188:2.1"
msgid "“Ahañhi, bhante, evaṃvādī evaṃdiṭṭhi: "
msgstr "“Sir, this is my doctrine and view: "

#. VAR: na upapādeti → na uppādeti (s1-3, pts1, mr)
msgctxt "an4.188:2.2"
msgid "‘yo koci parūpārambhaṃ vatteti, parūpārambhaṃ vattento sabbo so na upapādeti. "
msgstr "‘Whoever goes on complaining about others without giving any reasons "

msgctxt "an4.188:2.3"
msgid "Anupapādento gārayho hoti upavajjo’”ti. "
msgstr "is reprehensible and at fault.’” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an4.188:2.4"
msgid "“Parūpārambhañce, upaka, vatteti parūpārambhaṃ vattento na upapādeti, anupapādento gārayho hoti upavajjo. "
msgstr "“Upaka, if someone goes on complaining about others without giving a reason, they’re reprehensible and at fault. "

msgctxt "an4.188:2.5"
msgid "Tvaṃ kho, upaka, parūpārambhaṃ vattesi, parūpārambhaṃ vattento na upapādesi, anupapādento gārayho hosi upavajjo”ti. "
msgstr "But that’s what you do, so you’re reprehensible and at fault!” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an4.188:2.6"
msgid "“Seyyathāpi, bhante, ummujjamānakaṃyeva mahatā pāsena bandheyya; "
msgstr "“Sir, like a fish caught in a big trap just as it rises, "

#. VAR: mahatā vādapāsena → mahatā pāsena (mr)
msgctxt "an4.188:2.7"
msgid "evamevaṃ kho ahaṃ, bhante, ummujjamānakoyeva bhagavatā mahatā vādapāsena baddho”ti. "
msgstr "so the Buddha caught me in a big trap of words just as I rose up.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "an4.188:3.1"
msgid "“Idaṃ akusalanti kho, upaka, mayā paññattaṃ. "
msgstr "“Upaka, I’ve declared: ‘This is unskillful.’ "

msgctxt "an4.188:3.2"
msgid "Tattha aparimāṇā padā aparimāṇā byañjanā aparimāṇā tathāgatassa dhammadesanā—"
msgstr "And there are limitless words, phrases, and teachings of the Realized One about that: "

# NOTE: BB here has “for such and such reasons”. In the parallel passage at SN56.19 he had: “In this statement,”. I can’t see that either rendering is justified. It seems to me that here the construction itipi has a literal meaning “thus also …”, i.e. “this is another way of explaining that this is akusala.” It simply expands the previous phrase.
msgctxt "an4.188:3.3"
msgid "itipidaṃ akusalanti. "
msgstr "‘This is another way of saying that this is unskillful.’ "

msgctxt "an4.188:3.4"
msgid "Taṃ kho panidaṃ akusalaṃ pahātabbanti kho, upaka, mayā paññattaṃ. "
msgstr "I’ve declared: ‘The unskillful should be given up.’ "

msgctxt "an4.188:3.5"
msgid "Tattha aparimāṇā padā aparimāṇā byañjanā aparimāṇā tathāgatassa dhammadesanā—"
msgstr "And there are limitless words, phrases, and teachings of the Realized One about that: "

msgctxt "an4.188:3.6"
msgid "itipidaṃ akusalaṃ pahātabbanti. "
msgstr "‘This is another way of saying that the unskillful should be given up.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "an4.188:4.1"
msgid "Idaṃ kusalanti kho, upaka, mayā paññattaṃ. "
msgstr "I’ve declared that: ‘This is skillful.’ "

msgctxt "an4.188:4.2"
msgid "Tattha aparimāṇā padā aparimāṇā byañjanā aparimāṇā tathāgatassa dhammadesanā—"
msgstr "And there are limitless words, phrases, and teachings of the Realized One about that: "

msgctxt "an4.188:4.3"
msgid "itipidaṃ kusalanti. "
msgstr "‘This is another way of saying that this is skillful.’ "

msgctxt "an4.188:4.4"
msgid "Taṃ kho panidaṃ kusalaṃ bhāvetabbanti kho, upaka, mayā paññattaṃ. "
msgstr "I’ve declared: ‘The skillful should be developed.’ "

msgctxt "an4.188:4.5"
msgid "Tattha aparimāṇā padā aparimāṇā byañjanā aparimāṇā tathāgatassa dhammadesanā—"
msgstr "And there are limitless words, phrases, and teachings of the Realized One about that: "

msgctxt "an4.188:4.6"
msgid "itipidaṃ kusalaṃ bhāvetabban”ti. "
msgstr "‘This is another way of saying that the skillful should be developed.’” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "an4.188:5.1"
msgid "Atha kho upako maṇḍikāputto bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinanditvā anumoditvā uṭṭhāyāsanā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā padakkhiṇaṃ katvā yena rājā māgadho ajātasattu vedehiputto tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā yāvatako ahosi bhagavatā saddhiṃ kathāsallāpo taṃ sabbaṃ rañño māgadhassa ajātasattussa vedehiputtassa ārocesi. "
msgstr "And then Upaka the son of Maṇḍikā approved and agreed with what the Buddha said. He got up from his seat, bowed, and respectfully circled the Buddha, keeping him on his right. Then he went up to King Ajātasattu Vedehiputta of Magadha. He told the King of all they had discussed. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc6
msgctxt "an4.188:5.2"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, rājā māgadho ajātasattu vedehiputto kupito anattamano upakaṃ maṇḍikāputtaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "But Ajātasattu became angry and upset, and said to Upaka, "

msgctxt "an4.188:5.3"
msgid "“yāva dhaṃsī vatāyaṃ loṇakāradārako yāva mukharo yāva pagabbo yatra hi nāma taṃ bhagavantaṃ arahantaṃ sammāsambuddhaṃ āsādetabbaṃ maññissati; "
msgstr "“How rude of this salt-maker’s boy! How impolite and impudent of him to imagine he could attack the Blessed One, the perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha! "

msgctxt "an4.188:5.4"
msgid "apehi tvaṃ, upaka, vinassa, mā taṃ addasan”ti. "
msgstr "Get out, Upaka, go away! Don’t let me see you again.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an4.188:5.5"
msgid "Aṭṭhamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </p></article></section></body></html>
